HEADWORD: Emargination
<hw>E*mar`gi*na"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The act of
notching or indenting the margin, or the state of being so notched;
also, a notch or shallow sinus in a margin.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Emasculate</ent>⟦br⟧
